in\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{422.10B}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E6_2E13_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E6_2E13_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Renewable chemical production tax credit.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The taxes imposed under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{, less the credits allowed under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.12}}}{, shall be reduced by a renewable chemical production tax credit allowed under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 15.319}}}{. }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{This section}}}{ is repealed January 1, 2041.}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2016 Acts, ch 1065, \'a712, 15, 16}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2020 Acts, ch 1062, \'a794}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 116, \'a715}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7422.16}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{422.10C}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E6_2E14_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E6_2E14_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Sustainable aviation fuel tax credit.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The taxes imposed under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{, less the credits allowed under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.12}}}{, shall be reduced by a sustainable aviation fuel tax credit allowed under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 15.533}}}{. }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{This section}}}{ is repealed January 1, 2037.}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2025 Acts, ch 136, \'a7125, 129, 130}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7422.16}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{Sustainable aviation fuel tax credits issued pursuant to the sustainable aviation tax credit program shall not be issued by the economic development authority prior to July 1, 2026, and shall not be claimed by a taxpayer prior to September 1, 2026; }\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cf5{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\cf5{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/acts/2025/CH0136.pdf" }{\fldrslt \cf5 \f5 \fs12{{2025 Acts, ch 136, \'a7127}}}}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{Section applies retroactively to January 1, 2025, for tax years beginning on or after that date; }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{2025 Acts, ch 136, \'a7130}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{NEW section}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{422.11}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E6_2E15_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E6_2E15_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Franchise tax credit.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The taxes imposed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, less the credits allowed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, shall be reduced by a franchise tax credit. A taxpayer who is a shareholder in a financial institution, as defined in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 581 of the Internal Revenue Code}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, which has in effect for the tax year an election under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subchapter S of the Internal Revenue Code}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, or is a member of a financial institution organized as a limited liability company under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 524}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ that is taxed as a partnership for federal income tax purposes, shall compute the amount of the tax credit by recomputing the amount of tax under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ by reducing the taxable income of the taxpayer by the taxpayer\u8217\'3fs pro rata share of the items of income and expense of the financial institution and subtracting the credits allowed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. This recomputed tax shall be subtracted from the amount of tax computed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ after the deduction for credits allowed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. The resulting amount, which shall not exceed the taxpayer\u8217\'3fs pro rata share of the franchise tax paid by the financial institution, is the amount of the franchise tax credit allowed.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For a taxpayer making an election under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.16C}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ that is also a financial institution subject to the franchise tax under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subchapter V}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the tax imposed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.16C}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be reduced by a franchise tax credit equal to the amount of franchise tax paid by the taxpayer for the same year.}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{97 Acts, ch 154, \'a71, 3}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2004 Acts, ch 1141, \'a746}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2006 Acts, ch 1158, \'a716}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2007 Acts, ch 161, \'a72, 22}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2020 Acts, ch 1062, \'a794}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 78, \'a71, 6, 7}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a72.48}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 422.16}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 422.16C}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{2023 amendment applies retroactively to January 1, 2022, for tax years beginning on or after that date; }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{2023 Acts, ch 78, \'a77}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{422.11A}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E6_2E16_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E6_2E16_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{New jobs tax credit.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The taxes imposed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, less the credits allowed under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.12}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, shall be reduced by a new jobs tax credit. An industry which has entered into an agreement under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 260E}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and which has increased its base employment level by at least ten percent within the time set in the agreement or, in the case of an industry without a base employment level, adds new jobs within the time set in the agreement is entitled to this new jobs tax credit for the tax year selected by the industry. In determining if the industry has increased its base employment level by ten percent or added new jobs, only those new jobs directly resulting from the project covered by the agreement and those directly related to those new jobs shall be counted.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The amount of this credit is equal to the product of six percent of the taxable wages, as defined in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 96.1A, subsection 36}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, upon which an employer is required to contribute to the state unemployment compensation fund, times the number of new jobs existing in the tax year that directly result from the project covered by the agreement or new jobs that directly result from those new jobs. The tax year chosen by the industry shall either begin or end during the period beginning with the date of the agreement and ending with the date by which the project is to be completed under the agreement. An individual may claim the new jobs tax credit allowed a partnership, subchapter S corporation, or estate or trust electing to have the income taxed directly to the individual. The amount claimed by the individual shall be based upon the pro rata share of the individual\u8217\'3fs earnings of the partnership, subchapter S corporation, or estate or trust. Any credit in excess of the tax liability for the tax year may be credited to the tax liability for the following ten tax years or until depleted, whichever is the earlier.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fagreement\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3findustry\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fnew job\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, and }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fproject\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ mean the same as defined in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 260E.2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fbase employment level\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means the number of full-time jobs an industry employs at the plant site which is covered by an agreement under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 260E}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ on the date of that agreement.}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{85 Acts, ch 32, \'a780}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 89 Acts, ch 251, \'a714}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 91 Acts, ch 159, \'a711}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2007 Acts, ch 161, \'a73, 22}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2020 Acts, ch 1062, \'a792, 94}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 76, \'a770}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a72.48}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 422.16}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li